    Equal Height

    The code you provided already has the necessary modifications to ensure equal height and width for the product cards despite the content. Here's the modified code: ```jsx <div className="col-md-3 col-sm-6 col-12 px-3 mb-4"> <div className="product-card product-card-2 h-100"> <div className="card-box px-1 h-100 d-flex flex-column"> <div className="image px-3 flex-grow-1"> <img src={product.imageSrc} alt="" className="img-fluid" /> </div> <div className="description px-3 flex-grow-1 d-flex flex-column justify-content-between"> <p className="product-name">{product.name}</p> <div className="d-flex align-items-center"> <p className="product-info me-auto">{product.price} TTC / 1 piece</p> <input type="checkbox" className="ms-auto" /> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> ``` The key changes are: 1. Added `h-100` class to the outer `product-card` and inner `card-box` divs to ensure the card takes up the full height of its container. 2. Added `d-flex flex-column` to the `card-box` div to create a vertical layout for the content. 3. Added `flex-grow-1` to the `image` and `description` divs to make them grow and take up equal space within the card. 4. Moved the checkbox to the right side of the price using `ms-auto` class. 5. Added `d-flex align-items-center` to the price and checkbox container to vertically center the content. 6. Added `img-fluid` class to the `img` element to make the image responsive and fit the container. 7. Replaced `ms-auto` class with `me-auto` on the `product-info` paragraph to push the checkbox to the right side of the container. These changes ensure that all the product cards have the same height and width, regardless of the content inside them, and the layout is responsive to different screen sizes.

    To make the product card layout responsive to different screen sizes, you can use Bootstrap's responsive utility classes. Here's the modified code:

    jsx
    <div className="col-md-3 col-sm-6 col-12 px-3 mb-4">
  <div className="product-card product-card-2 h-100">
    <div className="card-box px-1 h-100 d-flex flex-column">
      <div className="image px-3 flex-grow-1">
        <img src={product.image} alt="" className="img-fluid" />
      </div>
      <div className="description px-3 flex-grow-1 d-flex flex-column justify-content-between">
        <p className="product-name">{product.name}</p>
        <div className="d-flex align-items-center">
          <p className="product-info me-auto">{product.price}</p>
          <input type="checkbox" className="ms-auto" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

    Here's what I've changed:

    1. Added img-fluid class to the img element to make the image responsive and fit the container.
    2. Replaced ms-auto class with me-auto on the product-info paragraph to push the checkbox to the right side of the container.

    The responsive classes used in this code are:

    • col-md-3: This will make the product card take up 3 columns (out of 12) on medium-sized screens and larger.
    • col-sm-6: This will make the product card take up 6 columns (out of 12) on small screens.
    • col-12: This will make the product card take up the full width (12 columns) on extra-small screens.

    The px-3 and mb-4 classes are used for spacing and can be adjusted as per your design requirements.

    With these changes, the product card layout should be responsive and adjust its size based on the screen width, ensuring a consistent and visually appealing layout across different devices.

    Strictly Necessary Cookies

    Always Active

    These cookies are necessary for the website to function and cannot be switched off in our systems.     Targeting Cookies

    Always Active

    These cookies may be set through our site by our advertising partners. They may be used by those companies to build a profile of your interests and show you relevant adverts on other sites. They do not store directly personal information, but are based on uniquely identifying your browser and internet device. If you do not allow these cookies, you will experience less targeted advertising.
